column1: Bitcoin rises, posting its third week of back-to-back gains: CNBC Crypto World
column2: CNBC Crypto World features the latest news and daily trading updates from the digital currency markets and provides viewers with a look at what's ahead with high-profile interviews, explainers, and unique stories from the ever-changing crypto industry. On today's show, Crypto World's Tanaya Macheel sits down with crypto experts to get the latest on tokenization, stablecoin adoption, and more.

column1: Bitcoin Exchange Reserves Hit 6-Year Low: What Does it Mean for Crypto Investors?
column2: In a noteworthy development, Bitcoin (BTC) exchange reserves on major cryptocurrency platforms like Coinbase, Binance, and Kraken have plummeted to their lowest levels in six years, signaling a significant shift in the crypto landscape. This decline in exchange-held Bitcoin has captured the attention of investors and analysts alike, prompting questions about its implications for the overall cryptocurrency market.

column1: Bitcoin, Ethereum and Dogecoin Trade Muted In Wake Of Fed Decision: A Look At The Crypto's Into The Weekend
column2: Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) was trading mostly flat during Friday's 24-hour trading session in the wake of this week's Federal Reserve meeting, where the central bank applied a pause on hiking interest rates. Ethereum (CRYPTO: ETH) and Dogecoin (CRYPTO: DOGE) also traded flat, in tandem with the S&P 500, while spot gold was lifting slightly, rising about 0.3%.
